ArrayList removeIf() method in java

[ArrayList removeIf() method in java](https://www.flowerbrackets.com/arraylist-removeif-method-in-java/)

Now letâ€™s see example on ArrayList removeIf() method.

import java.util.ArrayList;
public class ArrayListRemoveIfMethodExample
{
   public static void main(String[] args)
   {
      ArrayList<Integer> al = new ArrayList<Integer>();
      al.add(15);
      al.add(8);
      al.add(58);
      al.add(19);
      // remove numbers divisible by 2
      al.removeIf(n -> (n % 2 == 0));
      // print list
      for(int a : al)
      {
         System.out.println(a);
      }
   }
}
